  "text": "For thermal management of the printed circuit board (PCB) parts, the thermal resistance must be calculated, which is the ability of a material to resist the heat flow. In the case of electronic devices operating in vacuum, it is necessary to contemplate the fact that there is not thermal resistance with the air, so there is only thermal resistance between the PCB and each device [CITATION_1] .",
